The '''Strange Pear Gallery of Fine Arts''' is a community-run virtual art gallery in [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat|VRChat]], created by Oz Pearsall. It operates similarly to a physical small-town art gallery, allowing artists to submit and display their work. The gallery hosts monthly gallery show openings with live music, twice-weekly open houses, and a variety of special events. By its third anniversary in September 2025, over 140 artists had displayed nearly 2,000 pieces at the gallery, which had grown to more than 4,000 group members.<ref name="fandom">[https://vrchat-legends.fandom.com/wiki/Strange_Pear_Gallery_of_Fine_Arts "Strange Pear Gallery of Fine Arts"] on ''VRChat Legends Wiki''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>

== History ==
=== Founding and VRU Oasis era (2022–2024) ===
The Strange Pear Gallery opened on September 15, 2022, housed within [[Community:VRU Oasis|VRU Oasis]], a VRChat world created by TheCastle. Its first event lasted two hours.<ref name="fandom" /> Over time the gallery grew into a regular gathering point for the VRChat art community, described as one of several "virtual salons for users to attend and share work with."<ref name="immersivism-history">[https://www.immersivism.com/history "History"] on ''Immersivism''. Retrieved April 8, 2026.</ref>

=== Standalone world (2024–present) ===
In May 2024, the gallery announced it would leave the VRU Oasis to become a standalone VRChat world, citing space constraints in the original venue. A separate area called "The Pear Grove" was established in VRU 2.0 as a thank-you to TheCastle.<ref name="fandom" />

The new Strange Pear world, built by Spoonie and themed as a repurposed factory in the Appalachian Mountains, opened to the public on July 4, 2024, debuting with Gallery Show 22, "Hidden Realms," featuring a record 26 artists.<ref name="fandom" />

